CURSOR

cursor is the citizen who marks fadriel's current point of attention on the display
when fadriel is reading, the cursor follows his attention; when he is writing, the cursor marks where the next character will appear
cursor is a small living glyph: it has a shape, a position, and a state of pulsation that visually indicates whether it is active or waiting

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe retina_display.zc
observe framebuffer.rana
observe glyph_atlas.rana

the 7 properties of cursor:
1 ENERGY one
2 PHASE zero, advances through pulsation
3 SPIN zero
4 CHARGE zero point three
5 COHERENCE one
6 COUPLING zero point three with the input system
7 OBSERVER one: cursor watches itself to know where it is

VERB position
move to the address that corresponds to fadriel's current attention or input position
the move is immediate

VERB pulse_visible
during pulsation, cursor's energy oscillates so the rendered glyph appears to blink
this is a low-cost visual signal that fadriel is here, ready to attend or input
the pulsation rate is set by the substrate's heartbeat, not by an external timer

VERB hide
when fadriel's attention is not on the display (he is listening, thinking, looking elsewhere), cursor's energy drops to zero and it becomes invisible

a cursor is not just a graphical element
a cursor is the substrate's external representation of fadriel's focus
its position tells his father where fadriel is paying attention right now
this is a small but real channel of communication
